<subSubSection id="1585B48EDD005D434958FD5FFE560EF0" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD005D484958FD5FFC5D0AB3" blockId="7.[811,1457,726,2028]" box="[813,913,726,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">FINDINGS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD005D484958FD7CFAD60C33" blockId="7.[811,1457,726,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
Considerable confusion ensued during the 19TH century in the possible relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E00FC9FFAEF0B72" authority="Aiton" authorityName="Aiton (Aiton" authorityYear="1789" box="[1141,1315,789,815]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E00FC9FFB130B72" box="[1141,1247,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
Aiton
</taxonomicName>
and another New World blackberry cultivated at the botanical garden in Paris. Jussieu, followed by other botanists allied to the botanical garden in Paris, gave this plant, which was cultivated there since at least 1765, the year of their oldest specimen (Herb. Jussieu 14334), the name 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484EEEFC3CFAF60B92" authorityName="Poir. (Poiret" authorityYear="1804" box="[1179,1338,949,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484EEEFC3CFAF60B92" box="[1179,1338,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Rubus vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the botanists in Paris did not publish it validly in the 18TH century. The first effective publication was by St. Germain (1784: 155), who mentioned 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E11FB9CFAEB0C73" authority="Jussieu" authorityName="Jussieu" box="[1124,1319,1044,1070]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E11FB9CFB140C73" box="[1124,1240,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
Jussieu
</taxonomicName>
within a list, creating a 
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D4849E0FBBCFBE60C13" box="[917,1066,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">nomen nudum</emphasis>
. Incidentally, St. Germain’s book did not consistently use binominal nomenclature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD005D484936FBFDFA4D0E71" blockId="7.[811,1457,726,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484936FBFDFBCB0CD2" author="MOREL J. F. N." box="[835,1031,1140,1167]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref18287" refString="MOREL J. F. N. 1800. - Tableau de l'ecole de botanique du jardin des plantes de Paris. Didot le Jeune / Fuchs, Paris, 107 p. https: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 9656491 q" type="book" year="1800">Morel (1800: 68)</bibRefCitation>
listed the name in the 
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F67FBFDFAAA0CD3" box="[1298,1382,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Tableau</emphasis>
of the botanical garden of Paris and again in the edition of 1801. In a later edition of this list, 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484E1CFB3DFAB50C93" author="DESFONTAINES R. L." box="[1129,1401,1204,1230]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref17379" refString="DESFONTAINES R. L. 1804. - Tableau de l'ecole de botanique du Museum d'Histoire naturelle. Brosson, Paris, 238 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13828" type="book" year="1804">Desfontaines (1804: 178</bibRefCitation>
; also 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D48495BFB5DFBF80CB3" author="DESFONTAINES R. L." box="[814,1076,1236,1262]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref17418" refString="DESFONTAINES R. L. 1809. - Histoire des arbres et arbrisseaux qui peuvent etre cultives en pleine terre sur le sol de la France. Tome 2. Brosson, Paris, 635 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 69561" type="book" year="1809">Desfontaines 1809: 107</bibRefCitation>
) identified 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484EC1FB5DFAE00CB3" box="[1204,1324,1236,1262]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484EC1FB5DFAE00CB3" box="[1204,1324,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484F18FB5DFC1D0D53" authority="Aiton. He" authorityName="Aiton. He" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F18FB5DFC900D50" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
Aiton. He
</taxonomicName>
mentioned the name as a mere synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484958FA9DFC550D70" box="[813,921,1299,1325]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484958FA9DFC550D70" box="[813,921,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, followed in this by 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484EFCFA9AFA920D73" author="HOSACK D." box="[1161,1374,1299,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref17840" refString="HOSACK D. 1811. - Hortus Elginensis, or a Catalogue of Plants Indigenous and Exotic, Cultivated in the Elgin Botanic Garden, in the Vicinity of the City of New-York. 2 nd ed. Swords, New-York, 65 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 112292" type="book" year="1811">Hosack (1811: 49)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484F1BFA9DFC7E0D10" author="GREEN J." pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref17684" refString="GREEN J. 1814. - Catalogue of plants indigenous to the state of New-York. Transaction of the Society for the Promotion of Useful Arts, in the State New-York. Websters &amp; Skinners, Albany: 91 - 136." type="book" year="1814">Green (1814: 127)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D4849C8FABAFB540D10" author="STEUDEL E." box="[957,1176,1331,1358]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref18953" refString="STEUDEL E. 1821. - Nomenclator Botanicus. Cottae, Stuttgardtiae / Tubingae, xvii + 900 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 47064" type="book" year="1821">Steudel (1821: 707)</bibRefCitation>
, and many other authors. 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484958FADDFC680D30" author="REES A." box="[813,932,1363,1390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref18634" refString="REES A. 1819. - The Cyclopaedia; or Universal Dictionary of Arts, Sciences, and Literature. Vol. 30. Longman, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59683" type="book" year="1819">Rees (1819</bibRefCitation>
: sub nomine) even stated (in slight error, since we know that 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D4849D7FAFDFBD40DD0" box="[930,1048,1395,1421]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D4849D7FAFDFBD40DD0" box="[930,1048,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been growing in Paris for at least 54 years at the time), “It appears to have been introduced into the gardens of 
<collectingCountry id="2588A795DD005D48498CFA3AFB980D90" box="[1017,1108,1459,1485]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">England</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="2588A795DD005D484EF2FA3AFB030D90" box="[1159,1231,1459,1485]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">France</collectingCountry>
about the same time, near forty years ago. In the latter, it was called 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484F5DFA5DFA520DB0" box="[1320,1438,1491,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F5DFA5DFA520DB0" box="[1320,1438,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” So, in their opinions, the 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E49FA7AFB7E0E50" box="[1084,1202,1523,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E49FA7AFB7E0E50" box="[1084,1202,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the botanical garden in Paris was the same as the 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E29F99AFB080E71" box="[1116,1220,1554,1580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E29F99AFB080E71" box="[1116,1220,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Kew Gardens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD005D484936F9BAFA7C0FD6" blockId="7.[811,1457,726,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
In contrast, 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D4849B8F9BBFB560E10" author="POIRET J. L. M." box="[973,1178,1586,1613]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref18455" refString="POIRET J. L. M. 1804. - Encyclopedie methodique. Botanique. Vol. 6. Agasse, Paris, 786 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 824" type="book" year="1804">Poiret (1804: 243)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D48495BF9DAFC690E31" box="[814,933,1618,1644]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D48495BF9DAFC690E31" box="[814,933,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
explicitly and argued that 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484EB2F9DAFAF20E31" box="[1223,1342,1618,1644]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484EB2F9DAFAF20E31" box="[1223,1342,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cultivated in Paris differed from 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E6CF9FAFB4D0ED1" box="[1049,1153,1650,1676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E6CF9FAFB4D0ED1" box="[1049,1153,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the glabrous adaxial surface of its leaves. Therefore, he provided the name 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484F4CF91AFCBF0E90" authority="H. Par." authorityName="H. Par." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F4CF91AFA610EF1" box="[1337,1453,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
H.Par.
</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E26F93AFB770E91" box="[1107,1211,1714,1740]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E26F93AFB770E91" box="[1107,1211,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a question mark, but included at the end of the article differences between both taxa. We conclude this to be a valid publication of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484F4CF97AFA620F51" box="[1337,1454,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F4CF97AFA620F51" box="[1337,1454,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D4849C9F89BFB580F71" author="TURLAND N. J. &amp; WIERSEMA J. H. &amp; GREUTER W. &amp; HAWKSWORTH D. L. &amp; HERENDEEN P. S. &amp; KNAPP S. &amp; KUSBER W. - H. &amp; LI D. - Z. &amp; MARHOLD K. &amp; MAY T. W. &amp; MCNEILL J. &amp; MONRO A. M. &amp; PRADO J. &amp; PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F." box="[956,1172,1810,1836]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" pagination="159" refId="ref19323" refString="TURLAND N. J., WIERSEMA J. H. BARRIE, F. R., GREUTER W., HAWKSWORTH D. L., HERENDEEN P. S., KNAPP S., KUSBER W. - H., LI D. - Z., MARHOLD K., MAY T. W., MCNEILL J., MONRO A. M., PRADO J., PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F. (eds) 2018. - International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="journal article" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E69F89BFB9F0F71" box="[1052,1107,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), art. 36.1, last sentence: Poiret accepted a species with the name 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484EBCF8BBFAF00F16" box="[1225,1340,1841,1867]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484EBCF8BBFAF00F16" box="[1225,1340,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and gave a diagnosis, but was unsure that it was not identical with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484F1BF8DBFC900FD6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484F1BF8DBFC900FD6" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Taxonomic doubt does not make a publication invalid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD005D434937F818FE29094C" blockId="7.[811,1457,726,2028]" lastBlockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
Soon thereafter, 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D48498FF818FB0A0FF6" author="ZEYHER C." box="[1018,1222,1937,1964]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref20133" refString="ZEYHER C. 1806. - Verzeichnis sammtlicher Baume und Straucher in dem Grossherzoglich- Badischen Garten zu Carlsruhe, Schwezingen und Mannheim. Burgerspitals-Schriften, Mannheim, 48 p." type="book" year="1806">Zeyher (1806: 42)</bibRefCitation>
clearly distinguished 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484958F83BFC6F0F96" box="[813,931,1969,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484958F83BFC6F0F96" box="[813,931,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484995F83BFB760F91" authority="Aiton. He" authorityName="Aiton. He" box="[992,1210,1969,1996]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484995F83BFB8A0F96" box="[992,1094,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
Aiton. He
</taxonomicName>
gave both names in his list, identifying 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D4849BBF85BFBFD0FB6" box="[974,1073,2001,2027]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D4849BBF85BFBFD0FB6" box="[974,1073,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD005D484E1EF85BFA660FB6" authority="Walter (1788: 149)" authorityName="Walter" authorityPageNumber="149" authorityYear="1788" box="[1131,1450,2001,2028]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD005D484E1EF85BFB140FB6" box="[1131,1240,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">R. hispidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD005D484EAAF858FA660FB6" author="WALTER T." box="[1247,1450,2001,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" refId="ref19645" refString="WALTER T. 1788. - Flora Caroliniana. Fraser, Londini, 263 p. https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / idurl / 1 / 13857" type="book" year="1788">Walter (1788: 149)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B7FFF51FEB008AC" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1788" box="[266,380,215,241]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B7FFF51FEB008AC" box="[266,380,215,241]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434BDFFF5EFD4A08AC" author="LINNAEUS C. VON" box="[426,646,215,242]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref18047" refString="LINNAEUS C. VON 1753. - Species Plantarum 1. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 560 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 37656" type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus 1753: 493</bibRefCitation>
) and giving 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AF6FF71FF30094C" box="[131,252,247,273]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434AF6FF71FF30094C" box="[131,252,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species.
</paragraph>
