<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFE9EFCC409AD" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
Seringe (in 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434B61FE91FDDF096F" author="DE CANDOLLE A. P." box="[276,531,279,306]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref17314" refString="DE CANDOLLE A. P. 1825. - Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis. Vol. 2. Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 644 p. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 153297" type="book" year="1825">De Candolle 1825: 563</bibRefCitation>
f) considered 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D4348DCFE91FF65090C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D4348DCFE91FF65090C" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a variety of 
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434BFDFEB1FDCE090C" box="[392,514,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434BFDFEB1FE32090C" box="[392,510,311,337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">R. villosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
He gave as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AD0FED1FEDA092C" box="[165,278,343,369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434AD0FED1FEDA092C" box="[165,278,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B52FED1FE2E092C" authority="Vill." authorityName="Vill." box="[295,482,343,369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B52FED1FE6B092C" box="[295,423,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. hybridus</emphasis>
Vill.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434B83FEDEFD7A092C" author="VILLARS D." box="[502,694,343,369]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref19525" refString="VILLARS D. 1779. - Prospectus de l'histoire des plantes de Dauphine. Imprimerie royale, Grenoble, 49 p. https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / idurl / 1 / 15535" type="book" year="1779">Villars 1779: 46</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D4348B1FEDEFF6A09CC" author="VILLARS D." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref19563" refString="VILLARS D. 1785. - Flora Delphinalis, in GILIBERT J. E., Caroli Linnaei Systema plantarum Europae 1. Piestre &amp; Delamolliere, Coloniae-Allobrogum, vii + 127 p." type="book" year="1785">1785: 51</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434ACBFEFEFDAC09CC" authority="Bellardi (1793: 230)" authorityName="Bellardi" authorityPageNumber="230" authorityYear="1793" box="[190,608,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434ACBFEFEFEAC09CC" box="[190,352,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. glandulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434B1FFEFEFDAC09CC" author="BELLARDI L." box="[362,608,375,401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" refId="ref16572" refString="BELLARDI L. 1793. - Appendix ad Floram Pedemontanam. Joannes Michael Briolus, Augustae Taurinorum, 80 + vii p. https: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 976423" type="book" year="1793">Bellardi (1793: 230)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D4348D6FEFEFD0209EC" authority="Waldst. &amp; Kit. (Waldstein &amp; Kitaibel 1805: 150)" authorityName="Waldst. &amp; Kit. (Waldstein &amp; Kitaibel" authorityYear="1805" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D4348D6FEFEFCCA09CC" box="[675,774,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. hirtus</emphasis>
Waldst. &amp; Kit. (
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434B33FE1FFD0909EC" author="WALDSTEIN F. &amp; KITAIBEL P." box="[326,709,406,433]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="101 - 200" refId="ref19597" refString="WALDSTEIN F. &amp; KITAIBEL P. 1805. - Descriptiones et icones plantarum rariorum Hungariae 2. Schmidt, Viennae, 105 - 220, ill. 101 - 200. https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / idurl / 1 / 11187" type="book chapter" year="1805">Waldstein &amp; Kitaibel 1805: 150</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and associated the 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B51FE3EFE65098D" box="[292,425,438,465]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" rank="variety" variety="vulpinus">
var. 
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B3BFE3FFE65098D" box="[334,425,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B92FE3EFF6209AD" authority="Weihe (1819: 18)" authorityName="Weihe" authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="1819" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sprengelii">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B92FE3EFDA4098D" box="[487,616,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. sprengelii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="390E9AF4DD0B5D434805FE3FFF6209AD" author="WEIHE K. E. A." pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="17 - 20" refId="ref19677" refString="WEIHE K. E. A. 1819. - Rubus Sprengelii; ein noch unbeschriebener Strauch des Furstentums Minden. Flora 2: 17 - 20." type="journal article" year="1819">Weihe (1819: 18)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, all of Seringe’s identifications lack any basis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AECFE7FFD830A6D" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B34FE7EFE0D0A4D" box="[321,449,502,528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B34FE7EFE0D0A4D" box="[321,449,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in several collections in the herbarium of the Musée Botanique:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFDBFFDFD0ACD" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
1. “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AB3FDBFFE480A0D" box="[198,388,566,592]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">Rubus vulpinus</taxonomicName>
H.R.P.; 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B85FDBFFD520A0D" authority="Aiton. Michaux." authorityName="Aiton. Michaux." box="[496,670,566,592]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">Rubus villosus</taxonomicName>
? Aiton. Michaux.” Herb. Poiret in Herb. Moquin-Tandon. Herb. Cosson/Herb. Durand (P 
<date id="2921C1C5DD0B5D434BDCFDFFFDEC0ACD" box="[425,544,630,656]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" value="1718-03-14">03141718</date>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFD1FFDEA0A8D" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
2. “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AB0FD1FFDCE0AED" authority="Desf. H. P." authorityName="Desf. H. P." box="[197,514,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">Rubus vulpinus Desf. H.P.</taxonomicName>
” Herb. Cosson/Herb. Durand; Herb. Maire (P 
<date id="2921C1C5DD0B5D434BEBFD3FFDD90A8D" box="[414,533,694,720]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" value="1720-03-14">03141720</date>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFD5FFDF50BD2" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
3. “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AB3FD5CFE500AB2" box="[198,412,725,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">Rubus canadensis</taxonomicName>
…cosus fructo rubro Rubi f… facie. Cod. .. H.R. Paris. H.R. Paris. 1765. Julio. Dans les parterres.” (Jussieu scripsit); “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D43487AFC9CFCC50B6D" authority="Juss." authorityName="Juss." box="[527,777,789,816]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">Rubus vulpinus Juss.</taxonomicName>
h.r.p.” (Poiret scripsit). Another label: ‘An 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434816FCBCFF3C0B2D" authority="Ait. Kew." authorityName="Ait. Kew." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">Rubus villosus Ait. Kew.</taxonomicName>
2. 210. LW 2.1085. Poir.enc. 6. 243. n. 21?” (Poiret scripsit). Herb. Jussieu 14.334
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFC1CFE5D0B92" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
4. “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434ABDFC1CFED40BF2" box="[200,280,917,943]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Rubus</taxonomicName>
vulp. Envoyé de Newyorck”. Herb. De Lamarck (P00297334).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFC5DFCCB0C53" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
5. “ 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AB4FC5DFEB40BB3" box="[193,376,980,1006]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">Rubus vulpinus</taxonomicName>
. Hort. Par.” “Herb. Richard.” “folio tactu molissima semi-tomentosa. sprengelii”. Herb Drake.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEFB9DFE4C0D10" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
All these specimens belong to the species presently known as 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434A88FBBCFDBE0C12" authority="Porter. Because" authorityName="Porter. Because" box="[253,626,1076,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434A88FBBCFE790C13" box="[253,437,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
Porter. Because
</taxonomicName>
the description of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AACFBDCFE9A0C33" box="[217,342,1108,1134]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434AACFBDCFE9A0C33" box="[217,342,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was made by Poiret, the 
<typeStatus id="822459A7DD0B5D434801FBDCFD690C32" box="[628,677,1109,1135]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
must be selected from among specimens he had seen. From the list above, this is uncertain for specimens 2, 4 and 5. In addition, specimen 4 was not from the botanical garden in Paris. Thus, the choice of a 
<typeStatus id="822459A7DD0B5D434B9FFB5DFDD70CB3" box="[490,539,1236,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
falls to specimens 1 or 3. Both are ones that Poiret signed as 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434825FB7DFD010D50" box="[592,717,1267,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434825FB7DFD010D50" box="[592,717,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and on both he expressed his doubt about their conspecificity with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AB5FABDFE4C0D10" authority="Aiton." authorityName="Aiton (Aiton" authorityYear="1789" box="[192,384,1331,1357]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434AB5FABDFEE30D10" box="[192,303,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. villosus</emphasis>
Aiton.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AE9FADAFE5A0E10" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
Specimen 3 is only a primocane, and specimen 1 includes an inflorescence with a secondary branch with some simple leaves and beginning compound leaves. Because Jussieu, who first gave the name to the taxon, labeled specimen 3 as 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B59FA5DFE0C0DB0" box="[300,448,1491,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B59FA5DFE0C0DB0" box="[300,448,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and, moreover, because the inflorescence of specimen 1 is more characteristic for the identification of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434B0DF99AFE3A0E71" box="[376,502,1554,1580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434B0DF99AFE3A0E71" box="[376,502,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we selected this as the 
<typeStatus id="822459A7DD0B5D434AF3F9BBFF220E11" box="[134,238,1586,1612]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">lectotype</typeStatus>
(P 
<date id="2921C1C5DD0B5D434B7BF9BAFE490E10" box="[270,389,1587,1613]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" value="1718-03-14">03141718</date>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D20E705DD0B5D434AEEF9DAFE560EF0" blockId="12.[131,777,215,1709]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
Because 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434A8AF9DAFE4C0E31" box="[255,384,1618,1644]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulpinus">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434A8AF9DAFE4C0E31" box="[255,384,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. vulpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434826F9DAFF000ED0" authority="Porter" authorityName="Porter" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434826F9DAFCC50E31" box="[595,777,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
Porter
</taxonomicName>
, we can conclude this is an earlier legitimate synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="9A9F9C86DD0B5D434AAAF91AFE580EF1" box="[223,404,1682,1708]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="allegheniensis">
<emphasis id="6FEB3B17DD0B5D434AAAF91AFE580EF1" box="[223,404,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">R. allegheniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
